{{Quote|When lightning rushes over the evening plains,<br />I return to my cold den<br />with a thula rat in my jaws.<br />Then, I smell your sweet spoor<br />smeared on the bones by the cave's maw.<br />Then, then my head fins begin to tremble<br />And my tail sways majestically as my mating howl<br />begins to fill the hollow of the night.|C-3PO's translation of a Tchuukthai love poem|<ref name="COPL">''[[The Courtship of Princess Leia]]''</ref>}}
'''Tchuukthai''', also called '''Wharls''', were sapient ceratopsian quadrupeds from the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]].

==Biology==
This [[Reptile/Legends|reptilian]]<ref name="CSWE" /> quadruped species had a brutish appearance<ref name="POTJS" /> as hulking beings with thick, leathery skin and armor plating protecting their head, joints, and vital organs.<ref name="UAAWE" /> Bony spikes protruded from their shoulders and jaws, and they had large, clawed feet,<ref name="CSWE" /> wide-set eyes, flaring nostrils, and sharp fangs. Bristling fur covered their shoulders and back. An adult Tchuukthai stood at two meters at the shoulder, or three meters when standing upright on the hind legs.<ref name="UAAWE" /> Normally walking on all fours meant that individuals were unable to carry a weight heavier than two [[Kilogram/Legends|kilograms]] in either hand, but could carry much heavier weights, unbearable to certain other species, on their backs.<ref name="POTJS" /> The species had a lifespan of over three hundred years.<ref name="UAAWE" />

The Tchuukthai vocabulary of [[Tchuukthese]] consisted of grunts and growls.<ref name="POTJS" />

==Society and culture==
As a people, the Tchuukthai were contemplative and free-thinking. Some preferred to be left alone, and the species as a whole was secretive, though others displayed genuine interest in meeting new species. Though slow to anger and disdainful of conflict, Tchuukthai fought fiercely when sufficiently provoked, and could react with annoyance to other species' reactions to their appearance and size. Depending on demeanor, such reactions could otherwise elicit amusement.<ref name="UAAWE" />

Tchuukthai who consorted with other species typically wore clothing, while other members of the species chose not to.<ref name="UAAWE" />

==History==
The Tchuukthai were a rare species<ref name="EGPM">''[[The Essential Guide to Planets and Moons]]''</ref> originating on a [[Planet/Legends|planet]] deep in the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]], and information about the species and their world remained sparse and unreliable. Lacking any meaningful designation for the species, the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] [[Republic Bureau of Xenology|Bureau of Xenology]] arbitrarily named it ''Wharl'',<ref name="TOTJC" /> which was considered to be the original name of the species.<ref name="CSWE" /> The Tchuukthai were considered little more than beasts for centuries, with their brutish appearance and grunting vocabulary helping to perpetuate the myth, and indeed they were more than happy for the misconception to thrive to keep their intelligence a secret. Over the course of several centuries, the Tchuukthai were discovered more than once by explorers, though most avoided contact with these seemingly dangerous beasts. Those urged to learn more were met with vicious snarls and ferocious displays.<ref name="POTJS" />

The true intelligence of the Tchuukthai was only discovered when a [[Thon's Jedi Master|Jedi Master]] encountered the species and befriended the Tchuukthai later known as [[Thon]]. Learning much of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]], the Tchuukthai was interested in leaving his homeworld but feared that his people would be exploited if their true nature became known. The [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] gave his word to protect the secret of the Tchuukthai, and the species' existence remained little more than rumor across most of the galaxy,<ref name="POTJS" /> which remained the case by the [[New Republic era]].<ref name="UAAWE" />

The so-called Wharls referred to the origin point of the [[Lugubraa]] as the [[Stratos Distribution/Legends|Stratos Distribution]].<ref name="TUR">''[[The Unknown Regions]]''</ref>

A number of famous love poems were composed by Tchuukthai, although they translated poorly into Basic.{{Fact}} [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] once recited one of his favorite Tchuukthai love poems, considering it a beautiful masterpiece, and offered a translation to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] when prompted. However, Solo prevented the droid from reciting all five hundred thousand lines of the epic.<ref name="COPL" />

==Tchuukthai in the galaxy==
Befriended by a [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]], the Tchuukthai later known as [[Thon]] departed his homeworld and was instructed in the Jedi arts, eventually becoming a Jedi Master himself around the time of the [[Great Sith War/Legends|Great Sith War]].{{Fact}} For thousands of years, he was the only member of his species to leave his homeworld for the wider galaxy.<ref name="POTJS" /> Thon used the name "Wharl" for his species, hinting that it hid the former name of his kind for reasons he did not wish to discuss, though he refused to comment on the Bureau of Xenology's usage of the name as a species designation, and scientists gave up on their inquiries to the recluse. He also declined to answer questions about his origins from fellow Jedi Masters on [[Ossus/Legends|Ossus]],<ref name="TOTJC" /> and claimed that he was the last surviving member of his people.<ref name="JATM">>''[[Jedi Academy Training Manual]]''</ref> Since Thon's departure, it was believed possible that other Tchuukthai may have ventured away from their world, possibly as pets or zoological exhibits, though their existence was largely considered rumor across most of the galaxy.<ref name="POTJS" />

==Common Tchuukthai names==
*Bval<ref name="UAAWE" />
*Drol<ref name="UAAWE" />
